## 1. Test Failures 🚨 (Critical)

### 1A. [test_agent_runtime.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_agent_runtime.py) — Stale Internal Attribute Reference

**Tests:** [test_hot_swap_rolls_back_on_failed_healthcheck](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_agent_runtime.py#234-264), [test_hot_swap_audits_success](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_agent_runtime.py#266-303)
**Error:** `AttributeError: 'ModuleLoader' object has no attribute '_loaded_modules'`

**Root Cause:** The [ModuleLoader](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#86-642) class was refactored to store loaded modules in `self._state["loaded"]` (line 104 of [loader.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#L104)) behind a [loaded_modules](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#137-141) property (line 137). The two tests on [lines 240 and 278](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_agent_runtime.py#L240) still use [getattr(loader, "_loaded_modules")](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#89-98) — the **pre-refactor** name that no longer exists.

**Fix:** Replace [getattr(loader, "_loaded_modules")](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#89-98) with `loader.loaded_modules` (or `loader._state["loaded"]`) in both tests.

---

### 1B. [test_final_gap_coverage.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_final_gap_coverage.py) — Incomplete Test Fixture

**Test:** [test_validator_capability_undeclared_gap](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_final_gap_coverage.py#285-329)
**Error:** `assert <ErrorCode.MODULE_MANIFEST_INVALID: '4001'> == <ErrorCode.MODULE_CAPABILITY_UNDECLARED: '4004'>`

**Root Cause:** The test on [line 279](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_final_gap_coverage.py#L279) creates only `manifest.json` and `capabilities.json` but the [ModuleValidator.validate()](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/module_validator.py#L71) method requires **7 structural files** (`module.yaml`, `manifest.json`, `capabilities.json`, `permissions.json`, `cost_profile.json`, `signature.sig`, `entry.py`). The structural check fires first (raising `MODULE_MANIFEST_INVALID`) before the capability check is ever reached.

**Fix:** The test fixture must create all 7 required structural files, plus a valid signature and public key, so the validator reaches the capability audit phase where `MODULE_CAPABILITY_UNDECLARED` is raised.

